This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and language modeling, which are both subfields of computer science. The paper specifically investigates the difficulty of modeling different languages using current state-of-the-art NLP tools. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a new statistical model, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks, which are a type of neural network, so it could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses statistical analysis and modeling, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
